---
import LegalAnchorNav from "../components/LegalAnchorNav.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../content/site.js";

const sections = [
  { id: "what-the-app-uses", label: "What the App Uses" },
  { id: "why-data-is-used", label: "Why Data Is Used" },
  { id: "ai-fallback", label: "AI-Assisted Fallback" },
  { id: "support-requests", label: "Support & Deletion Requests" },
];
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Closed-beta privacy summary for CategoryFix, aligned with the current Shopify app implementation."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Privacy"
    title="Privacy Wording Should Stay as Narrow as the Product Behavior."
    intro="This privacy summary is tailored to the current closed beta. It describes the data handling implied by the present repository and should be reviewed again before broader launch."
  />

  <div class="legal-layout">
    <LegalAnchorNav items={sections} />

    <div class="legal-panel">
      <section id="what-the-app-uses">
        <h2>What the App Uses</h2>
        <p>
          CategoryFix connects to Shopify so it can read product information needed to detect
          missing or likely-wrong product categories and, when a merchant confirms changes, write
          approved category updates back to Shopify.
        </p>
        <p>
          Current product behavior includes scan records, recommendation findings, apply jobs,
          rollback jobs, audit events, and webhook processing data needed to keep the workflow
          explainable and reversible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="why-data-is-used">
        <h2>Why Data Is Used</h2>
        <p>
          The app uses Shopify product fields such as title, product type, vendor, tags,
          collections, and existing category state to generate reviewable category recommendations.
          It also stores operational records so merchants can inspect what changed and roll back
          approved writes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="ai-fallback">
        <h2>AI-Assisted Fallback</h2>
        <p>
          AI assistance is optional in the current product. When enabled, it is intended only for
          deterministic no-safe outcomes and is presented as advisory support rather than definitive
          platform truth.
        </p>
        <p>
          CategoryFix does not autonomously apply AI-only category updates. Merchant review remains
          required before any category write occurs.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because this beta may evolve before wider release, any final production privacy policy
          should confirm the exact model configuration, data flow, and retention details in use at
          that time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="support-requests">
        <h2>Support & Deletion Requests</h2>
        <p>
          CategoryFix implements Shopify compliance webhook handling and expects published privacy
          behavior to stay consistent with those flows. Questions about beta privacy handling can be
          sent to <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.supportEmail}`}>{siteConfig.supportEmail}</a>.
        </p>
        <p>No live billing is enabled in the current closed beta.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>
